oc:kn_04fe34b3 a oc:FallbackStrategy,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When problem boundaries are unclear" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If you don't know what's broken yet (exploratory debugging), do NOT dispatch parallel agents — investigate sequentially first to understand the problem space." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Parallel dispatch requires knowing that problems are independent; premature dispatch wastes agents on potentially related issues" .

oc:kn_511510dd a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating whether to use parallel agents" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use parallel dispatch when you have 3+ test files failing with different root causes, multiple subsystems broken independently, or problems that can be understood without context from others." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Parallel dispatch saves time proportional to the number of independent domains — 3 problems solved in time of 1" .

oc:kn_5d6424a7 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When crafting agent prompts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never give agents vague or overly broad tasks like 'Fix all the tests'. Each agent prompt must be focused, self-contained, and specific about expected output." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Vague prompts cause agents to get lost or make unintended changes; specificity ensures focused, productive work" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_74171f30 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before dispatching parallel agents" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do NOT use parallel agents when failures are related, when agents would share state, or when editing the same files. Related failures should be investigated together." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Related failures may share root causes — fixing one might fix others. Shared state causes conflicts between agents." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8c3899e2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After all agents complete their tasks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "After agents return: review each summary, check for conflicts (did agents edit same code?), run full test suite, and spot-check results since agents can make systematic errors." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Independent agents may produce conflicting changes or systematic errors that only appear when integrated together" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_975062fe a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When dispatching parallel agents" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Dispatch one agent per independent problem domain. Each agent should never inherit session context or history — construct exactly what they need." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Isolated context keeps agents focused, prevents scope creep, and preserves the coordinator's context for integration work" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a491e934 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing agent instructions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each agent prompt should include: specific scope (one test file or subsystem), clear goal, constraints (what NOT to change), and expected output format." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Well-structured prompts prevent agents from wandering, over-refactoring, or returning unactionable results" .

